docs.lead_paragraph: The number of deaths during the year 1851 was 18,934. which is 15 per cent, over the mortality of 1850; the latter, however, was a year of unusual health. The average of deaths was one to fifty-one and ninety-eight hundreths (51 98) of the population, or less than two per cent.

docs.lead_paragraph: SLEIGHING IN NEW-YORK.--The streets of New - York were all alive yesterday with merry sleigh riders. The omnibus proprietors, who had began to think that their yearly sleighing harvest would fail, got out their gaily painted and mammoth sized sledges; the hack-men betook themselves to runners, as did also the milkmen, cartmen, and grocers.

headline.main: The Military Convention at Syracuse.; SECOND DAY.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Military Convention reassembled at 9 o'clock this morning. Col. SCROGGS asked, Was it a Convention or an Association? The PRESIDENT decided it was a Convention until another organization was effected. Col. SCROGGS stated that the compensation to soldiers was insufficient.
